## ✅ STEP 2: Confirm proxy is intercepting `/api`

Now we’ll **prove Vite is catching the request**.

### 🔎 Add proxy logging

```ts
proxy: {
  '/api': {
    target: env.VITE_API_GATEWAY_URL,
    changeOrigin: true,
    configure: (proxy) => {
      proxy.on('proxyReq', (proxyReq, req) => {
        console.log(
          '[PROXY HIT]',
          req.method,
          req.url
        );
      });
    }
  }
}
```

Restart Vite again.

***

### ▶ Trigger request (browser or code)

```ts
fetch('/api/quote/v1/quote/d2ckmbl/saveQuote');
```

### ✅ EXPECTED TERMINAL LOG

    [PROXY HIT] POST /api/quote/v1/quote/d2ckmbl/saveQuote

### ❌ If NOTHING logs

➡️ Proxy is **NOT matching**

#### Common causes:

| Issue                             | Fix                                |
| --------------------------------- | ---------------------------------- |
| Request doesn’t start with `/api` | Must start exactly with `/api`     |
| Used full URL                     | Use `/api/...` only                |
| Wrong dev server port             | Check Vite actually runs on `5713` |

